<author><name><![CDATA[Roth]]></name></author>
<updated>2009-11-07T11:38:39-07:00</updated>
<published>2009-11-07T11:38:39-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5694&amp;p=52249#p52249</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5694&amp;p=52249#p52249"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[How to create .chr file?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5694&amp;p=52249#p52249"><![CDATA[
I made a little command line program that creates blank binary files that I use for CHR work. Download the program called 'makebin' on this page:<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://robertlbryant.com/programs/cpp.htm">http://robertlbryant.com/programs/cpp.htm</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Run it from the command line, enter 4 for your file size, and hit enter. Then open Tile Layer Pro, set 'Files of type' at the bottom to All Files (*.*), open the file you made with makebin, click View -&gt; Type -&gt; NES.  Start editing your file, and don't forget to save!<br /><br />Hope that helps a little.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=174">Roth</a> — Sat Nov 07, 2009 11:38 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
